This course allowed me to utilize some of the most common testing methodologies within the software development life cycle. Specifically,
I spent much of my time using unit testing within java JUnit tests. These projects taught me how to better formulate my process
through test driven development, to ensure my code was function, secure, and met the desires and requirements of the customer.

Much of the interpretation of user needs comes from the many interactions with the customer, ensuring that questions are asked
and clarification is gained from their desires. Things like basic security, types of input, basic application functionality,
and some edge cases can be taken from the interections with the customer/user before even beginning the project.

I approach designing software aggressively, and directly. I like to take what the customer needs, and ensure that they are
given a solid, secure, error free baseline to work from, so that we can both improve on the software as needed from that baseline.
